<h2> Booking meetups </h2>
<h4> Travelers will request meetups with you if they are interested in your service. Once the request is sent, it will show up in your meetup list and you can decide to respond available or no. If you respond available, the traveler will have the ability to book the meetup. A 2-day advance notice is required to cancel any booked meetups.<br/><br/> You can also look for potential travelers on the  Corkboard and respond to posts that match the service you can offer in your city.</h4><br/><br/>
<h2> Safety </h2>
<h4>tiniHost wants you to have a safe and fun experience meeting travelers. Unfortunately, we do not have the infrastructure to screen the mental health of all of our users. So please, use your common sense when meeting strangers. tiniHost highly recommends meeting during daylight hours and in public places, at least for your initial meetup. Don't be afraid to leave or use the appropriate authorities when feeling uncomfortable or threatened by someone. Please contact our team if you ever run into problems with anyone and we'll make sure to investigate and blacklist the user if necessary.</h4>
